<br>
I'm lvl 36. my friend just started playing. He's a lvl 2 wiz. I wanna know if I can help him get XP like this...<br>
<br>
use the 29 DS (Inferno Shield - CR says its 15dmg)<br>
let him melee, nuke the mob to 50%hp then me kill it.<br>
<br>
my question is how long i can do this for. of course, he cant melee for long and eventually will need to do something else. how reliable is that lvl 4 root? (how long does it usually last) And, is there a more effecient way to do this? I know we're not a &quot;PL&quot;ing class but I really wanna group with my friend asap (I know it's a while, though) Sorry if u guys get mad at me for not talking about PoP =P <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gamrok>Gamrok</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 347<br> <font color=#333333>(10/25/02 3:19:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7552.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Helping lower lvls get XP</span><hr size=1> The Inferno Shield damage is not credited to him, so you'd need to wait longer than 50% to nuke.<br>
<br>
What I would suggest is just DSing him and letting him run around meleeing stuff while you watch his back.  Once is becomes a hassle for him to melee, if you have the money then try having your pet slice into a bunch of mobs, being careful not to kill any of them but getting them low on health (can also be done against just one mob) then /pet get lost, DS your friend, and let him go to work.  Just stick to killing mass blues, and don't try to get him mixed up with anything too tough since he isn't a melee class. <p>&lt;FONT Face=&quot;Arial&quot; size=&quot;-1&quot;&gt;<br>
