Ayonae Ro</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lordgojirax>LordGojirax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 168<br> <font color=#333333>(10/25/02 4:07:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7552.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.jackntracie.com/images/gojhead.jpg width=98 height=126></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Helping lower lvls get XP</span><hr size=1> Damage shields are AWESOME to power level with BECAUSE the damage isn't credited to anyone.<br>
<br>
Damage shield YOURSELF... tank the mob and let him nuke from a distance.<br>
<br>
Even works better if you can get a Cleric to tank, plate armor and heals make it perfect. (As does Atone and buffs for the Wizard.)<br>
<br>
Basically, get KEI and POTG for the Wizard and you DS tank while your Wizard friend runs up and either whacks once with a stick or nukes.<br>
<br>
Have him continue to use a low level nuke (At least low enough level that he can stand and nuke and not really lose much mana with KEI.) and his spell casting skills will raise well too.<br>
<br>
When he hits level 20 get one of those Pottery click nuke rings. Have him use that for the exp when he's LOM.<br>
<br>
*EDIT*<br>
Another thing. Summon up an earth pet and park him just out of aggro range, that way if you need to you can run to him for help, but he won't run up and kill whatever you are attacking all the time.<br>
