<br>
You only start EQ once, and some of my first memories of playing are the most priceless.  I'm spending a lot of time exploring the new planes and pushing myself to the limit just as a way to recapture those first experiences.<br>
<br>
Otherwise if your hell-bent on powerleveling, the trick of reclaiming or /pet get lost, works perfectly, as your pet get attributed the damage dealt, so the wizard (or any class with an evocation spell really) can finish it off with one nuke, and get full experience.  Once you get the timing down, of course.  I got a wizard friend of mine (4th generation twink) up to 50th in about 4 days with that method, and without clarity or koadic or any outside buffs, so this does work, and now I have a friend who teleports me around all the time.<br>
<br>
